The paper discusses the use of neural network approaches for automatic question generation and question answering. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with NLP. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories as they cover ML techniques. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as it covers neural network approaches. Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category but still relevant as it covers techniques for retrieving information from text.
